const projects$1 = /* @__PURE__ */ JSON.parse(`{"paquita-pilates":{"category":"Client Web Project","title":"Paquita Pilates \u2014 Website & Booking Platform","description":"An instructor with deep expertise and a down-to-earth teaching style \u2014 but a digital presence falling behind. For paquitapilatesreformer.com, I developed brand identity, UX architecture, and a custom booking system that feels as personal as walking through her studio door.","longDescription":"**The Challenge**\\\\n\\\\nPaquita Pilates is a boutique Reformer and Classical Pilates studio in Stuttgart-Ost, offering private, duo, and small-group sessions. Despite offering a premium, deeply personal experience, the studio lacked cohesive brand identity, a professional website, and class bookings were managed manually \u2014 creating friction for both clients and instructors.\\\\n\\\\nThe core question: how do you translate the calm, intentional, body-conscious spirit of a boutique Pilates studio into a complete brand and digital experience that attracts the right clients and makes day-to-day studio management effortless?\\\\n\\\\n**1. Objectives**\\\\n\\\\nBuilding identity and digital infrastructure from the ground up:\\\\n\\\\n- **Brand Development:** Logo, color system, visual language \u2014 consistent across all touchpoints\\\\n- **Website:** Digital presence communicating philosophy, class offerings, and team\\\\n- **Booking System:** Integrated platform with self-service for clients and admin tools for instructors\\\\n\\\\nLive at: paquitapilatesreformer.com\\\\n\\\\n**2. Scope of Work**\\\\n\\\\nThree interconnected pillars:\\\\n\\\\n- **Brand Identity & Design System:** Complete branding from scratch \u2014 logo, typography, color palette. Flexible application across digital (website, Instagram) and physical materials.\\\\n- **Website Design & Development:** Custom website as primary digital presence \u2014 calm layouts, purposeful whitespace, clear calls-to-action.\\\\n- **Digital Booking System:** Dual-architecture:\\\\n  - **Client-facing:** Account creation, browse and book classes, personal schedule, booking management\\\\n  - **Admin/Instructor-facing:** Class creation and editing, capacity management, participant lists\\\\n\\\\n**3. Design System**\\\\n\\\\nThe visual system captures the studio's dual nature: grounded and physical on one side, mindful and spiritual on the other.\\\\n\\\\n**Logo:** A central all-seeing eye \u2014 symbol of awareness and inner vision \u2014 paired with wings and ornamental detail, set within soft shapes. The wordmark motto 'RETURN TO LIFE' (Joseph Pilates' original method name) completes the timeless, contemporary emblem.\\\\n\\\\n**Typography:**\\\\n\\\\n- **Metanoia** (Display): A high-contrast editorial serif. The name means 'transformative change of heart' \u2014 direct mirror of the studio philosophy. Elegance for headlines.\\\\n- **Poppins** (UI): Geometric sans-serif for body text and interface elements \u2014 modern and readable\\\\n\\\\n**Color Palette (7 colors):**\\\\n\\\\n- **Olive Gold (#86703f):** Earthy depth, accent for structure\\\\n- **Warm Taupe (#937955):** Neutral mid-tone\\\\n- **Terracotta Copper (#b27d55):** Warmest tone, logo and key brand moments\\\\n- **Cream White (#f0f1ed):** Primary background \u2014 soft, breathable\\\\n- **Soft Teal (#97cbcc):** Only cool tone \u2014 clarity and calm, highlight\\\\n- **Muted Rose Taupe (#968173):** Quiet tone for secondary text\\\\n- **Warm Grey (#bbbbaf):** Versatile neutral for surfaces\\\\n\\\\nThe result: a color world that communicates the sensory studio experience \u2014 natural materials, soft light, stillness.\\\\n\\\\n**4. Technology & Implementation**\\\\n\\\\n- **Frontend:** Vue.js + Ionic for cross-platform experience\\\\n- **Backend:** Node.js + MongoDB API, custom built\\\\n- **Real-time Scheduling:** Instant availability and confirmation\\\\n- **Credit System:** Flexible prepaid model for clients\\\\n\\\\n**5. Results & Outlook**\\\\n\\\\nBranding and website are complete and live. The booking system is in active development and being rolled out incrementally.\\\\n\\\\nPlanned extensions:\\\\n\\\\n- Automated waitlist management\\\\n- Credit/package systems\\\\n- Push notifications for class reminders\\\\n\\\\n**My Contribution:** Complete branding, UX architecture, UI design, and full-stack implementation. A booking platform that doesn't feel like off-the-shelf software \u2014 but like a conversation at the studio door.","tags":["Web Design","Development","Booking System"],"meta":{"role":"Full-Stack & Design","client":"Paquita Pilates"},"imageAlt":"Paquita Pilates Stuttgart App","imageAlt2":"Paquita Pilates Mobile View","gallery":{"1":"Home screen \u2014 class schedule, credit balance, and instant booking in one view","2":"Studio dashboard \u2014 desktop view for managing classes, clients, and schedules"},"features":{"1":{"title":"Smart Scheduling","desc":"Real-time availability with instant confirmation \u2014 no back-and-forth, just flow."},"2":{"title":"Seamless Anywhere","desc":"From desktop to smartphone, the experience stays elegant and intuitive."},"3":{"title":"Studio Identity","desc":"Visual language reflecting the authentic warmth and earthy tones of the physical space."},"4":{"title":"Dual Perspectives","desc":"Separate interfaces for clients and instructors, each optimized for their needs."}}},"hiqer":{"category":"Academic Project","title":"HIQER \u2014 Persuasion for the Outdoors","description":"What if your phone made you put your phone away? HIQER turns outdoor exploration into a competitive quest \u2014 GPS triggers, XP, leaderboards, and a companion Watch app designed so the screen stays in your pocket.","longDescription":"**The Challenge**\\\\n\\\\nHow can a device be used to connect physical nature exploration with digital added value in a way that creates long-term user engagement? The goal: increasing intrinsic motivation of hikers through digital design.\\\\n\\\\n**1. Concept & Device Strategy**\\\\n\\\\nThe deliberate choice was the smartphone as the mobile link between user and environment. Through IoT approaches and location-based services, the hiking trail becomes interactive:\\\\n\\\\n- **Object Networking:** QR codes at physical markers or GPS recognition connect the smartphone with each 'Spot'\\\\n- **Digital Layer in Nature:** The phone as a window to history \u2014 information about cultural sites, trail facts, or 'Then-vs-Now' comparisons available on-site\\\\n\\\\n**2. Psychological Strategy (Persuasive Design)**\\\\n\\\\nTo maintain motivation continuously, HIQER uses targeted design mechanisms:\\\\n\\\\n- **Cognitive Curiosity:** The 'thirst for knowledge' is satisfied through exclusive, location-bound content at destination points\\\\n- **Gamification & Rewards:** Experience points for reached spots, a level system enables Social Comparison \u2014 users compare progress and motivate each other\\\\n- **Ambition & Fitness:** Real-time fitness data (e.g. step counter) coupled with quests and social comparisons awaken personal ambition\\\\n\\\\n**3. Synergy of Nature and Technology**\\\\n\\\\nThe concept goes beyond the purely digital layer and addresses physiological needs. Networking with local infrastructure offers discount codes for nearby restaurants \u2014 a targeted connection of extrinsic reward and real benefit after hiking.\\\\n\\\\n**4. The Result**\\\\n\\\\nHIQER transforms classic hiking into a connected experience. The smartphone shifts from distraction factor to essential tool for discovery, fitness, and social interaction in nature.\\\\n\\\\n**My Methodology:** Conducted guerrilla field tests, mapped three distinct personas, iterative prototype development until friction disappeared. The Apple Watch companion was the key insight \u2014 glanceable cues and haptic feedback meant the phone never needed to leave the pocket. Highest marks. Presented at the HdM Digital Innovation Forum.","tags":["UX Design","Gamification","Persuasive Design"],"meta":{"focus":"Nature & Movement","feature":"Quests & Ranking"},"imageAlt":"HIQER App","imageAlt2":"HIQER Watch","gallery":{"1":"Quest map \u2014 GPS-triggered outdoor challenges scattered across the city","2":"Active quests \u2014 XP tracking, progress bars, and upcoming rewards","3":"Leaderboard \u2014 social ranking to spark friendly competition between explorers","4":"Apple Watch companion \u2014 glanceable navigation and haptic cues, phone stays in your pocket"},"features":{"1":{"title":"Location Triggers","desc":"QR spots and GPS unlock contextual content exactly where curiosity strikes."},"2":{"title":"Playful Progress","desc":"XP, levels, and leaderboards transform every walk into an achievement."},"3":{"title":"Cross-Device Flow","desc":"Smartwatch navigation means your phone stays in your pocket while exploring."},"4":{"title":"Curiosity Engine","desc":"Historical storytelling and local secrets revealed at exact coordinates."}}},"kischde":{"category":"Sustainable Platform","title":"Kischde \u2014 Trade Within Trust","description":"No marketplace noise. No strangers. Just a circle of people you trust \u2014 and the things you no longer need. Kischde is a swipe-first trading app built on the belief that giving should feel better than selling.","longDescription":"**The Challenge**\\\\n\\\\nExisting secondhand platforms create friction for low-value items through high effort: detailed descriptions, negotiations, shipping, pricing concerns. The result? These items end up in trash instead of new hands.\\\\n\\\\nOur vision: a central digital 'freebie box'. An uncomplicated, fast, and personal alternative enabling reuse within private circles through the friendship principle.\\\\n\\\\n**1. Project Approach and Strategy**\\\\n\\\\nTimeline: March to June 2021 (Mobile Media application project).\\\\n\\\\nMVP Focus: Due to the tight schedule, we defined a Minimum Viable Product concentrating on core functions:\\\\n\\\\n- **Frontend development** with Vue.js and Ionic\\\\n- **Backend integration** for data persistence\\\\n- **UX design process** for usability enhancement\\\\n- **Custom launcher** for cross-platform mobile web app\\\\n\\\\nConscious exclusions (Non-Scope): Payment system, chat function, WCAG compliance, complex animations \u2014 all excluded to maintain focus on the core experience.\\\\n\\\\n**2. Scope and Team Contribution**\\\\n\\\\nThe interdisciplinary team was divided into organization, design, and development.\\\\n\\\\n**My Contribution:**\\\\n- Led the **Project Scope Definition**\\\\n- Core member of the **development team** (Vue.js/Ionic)\\\\n- Co-created the UX system design\\\\n\\\\nCore scope delivered:\\\\n\\\\n- **Home feed** with trusted circle items\\\\n- **Profile page** with personal listings\\\\n- **Home screen** as central navigation\\\\n- **Swipe-first interface** for minimal cognitive load\\\\n\\\\n**3. The Result**\\\\n\\\\nA functional MVP that drastically simplifies the handover process. Instead of marketplace anonymity: circles of trusted people. Instead of complex negotiations: simple swipe gestures.\\\\n\\\\nThe application provides an intuitive trading platform for private contexts \u2014 developed with focus on sustainability through reuse rather than disposal.","tags":["Vue.js & Ionic","MongoDB","UX System"],"meta":{"role":"Full-Stack Developer","team":"5 People"},"imageAlt":"Kischde App","imageAlt2":"Kischde App Screen 2","gallery":{"1":"Home feed \u2014 items shared within your trusted circle, no marketplace noise","2":"Profile view \u2014 your listings, exchange history, and trust connections"},"features":{"1":{"title":"Circle-Based","desc":"Exchange only within trusted friend groups \u2014 familiar faces, zero friction."},"2":{"title":"Circular by Design","desc":"Every trade extends product lifecycles and reduces waste naturally."},"3":{"title":"Mobile-First","desc":"Platform-agnostic architecture. Your items, always within reach."},"4":{"title":"Effortless Flow","desc":"Intuitive gestures for giving and requesting \u2014 no forms, no friction."}}},"steal-back":{"category":"Game Design & Concept","title":"Steal Back \u2014 Play as Protest","description":"A 2D pixel-art puzzle platformer where activism meets gameplay. Uncover colonial art theft by day, reclaim history by night. Based on true events that demand to be remembered.","longDescription":"Steal Back is a game concept that emerged from a research project on colonial art restitution. Rather than write a paper, I designed a playable argument. The day/night cycle is the mechanic: during the day, the player investigates \u2014 reading archives, speaking to NPCs, building a case. At night, they act \u2014 using stealth and puzzle-solving to recover the stolen objects and return them. Each piece you reclaim triggers a factual summary of the real theft it represents. The pixel art style was chosen deliberately \u2014 it codes as 'safe and playful' while carrying genuinely heavy subject matter.","tags":["Game Design","Pixel Art","2D Platformer"],"meta":{"genre":"Puzzle Platformer","basis":"Historical Events"},"imageAlt":"Steal Back Game","features":{"1":{"title":"Day & Night","desc":"Information gathering transforms into stealth action as darkness falls."},"2":{"title":"Puzzle Mastery","desc":"Environmental challenges demanding strategy, timing, and creativity."},"3":{"title":"Historical Grounding","desc":"Every artwork tells a true colonial story \u2014 play to remember."},"4":{"title":"Pixel Artistry","desc":"Hand-crafted retro aesthetics with modern depth and atmosphere."}}},"beast":{"category":"Interdisciplinary Academic Project","title":"B.E.A.S.T. \u2014 Charging with Character for Mercedes-AMG","description":"How do you bring heartbeat back to electric vehicles? In a Winter 2022/23 interdisciplinary project, our HdM Stuttgart team collaborated with Mercedes-AMG to prototype multimodal charging experiences \u2014 light, haptics, and sound \u2014 validated through real user testing in the Mobile Lab.","longDescription":"**The Problem: The 'Ping' Paradox.**\\\\n\\\\nEV charging is silent. Plug in, beep, wait. The emotional heartbeat that combustion engines provided \u2014 the roar, the vibration, the feeling of power \u2014 is completely absent. For AMG customers, this creates a gap in brand perception.\\\\n\\\\n**1. Analysis & Briefing**\\\\n\\\\nTogether with Mercedes-AMG and Mercedes-Benz, we defined a clear mission for the Winter 2022/23 semester: make the car feel 'alive' during charging. Our target group analysis identified two archetypes: the 'Performer' (status-oriented, tech-savvy, efficiency-focused) and the 'Hedonist' (experience-oriented, comfort-seeking, trend-conscious).\\\\n\\\\n**2. Ideation & Prototyping**\\\\n\\\\nOur interdisciplinary HdM team developed three sound categories: 'BEAST' (organic, animalistic, heartbeat sounds), 'PING' (comfortable, familiar, chimes), and 'Futuristic' (sci-fi, synthetic, energetic). In parallel, we designed lighting concepts \u2014 from fiery red (BEAST) to blue energy flow (Futuristic).\\\\n\\\\nThe technical implementation was ambitious: LED animations via ESP32 controllers for grille and side lights, haptic feedback through magnets at the charging connector (the 'suction effect'), plus proximity detection via scanners and tags.\\\\n\\\\n**3. Testing Methodology**\\\\n\\\\nWe conducted two separate testing phases: Card-sorting with 19 participants to categorize sounds (sorting 20 sounds into charging phases) and UEQ-S lab tests with 15 users in the Mobile Lab. We evaluated attribute pairs like obstructive vs. supportive, complicated vs. simple, boring vs. exciting.\\\\n\\\\n**4. Results & Insights**\\\\n\\\\nThe results surprised us: The futuristic lighting concept (blue energy flow from charging port into car) achieved the highest scores for pragmatism (M=1.767) and hedonics (M=1.926). BEAST sounds were often perceived as 'creepy' or outside the comfort zone \u2014 only 55% could categorize them correctly.\\\\n\\\\nColor psychology played a decisive role: users intuitively associate blue with electricity and energy flow, while red signals danger or 'stop'. The Performer persona recognized futuristic sounds 100% of the time, while Hedonists were more open to familiar 'ping' sounds.\\\\n\\\\n**5. Reflection & Recommendations**\\\\n\\\\nThe 'Perfect Experience' according to our findings: blue light animation (Futuristic) combined with subtle BEAST plug-in sound. Haptic feedback was rated neutral to positive but needs refinement.\\\\n\\\\nUsers want personalization \u2014 volume control, off-switch, individual charging status displays. Methodologically, one limitation remains: our test group (predominantly 18-25 year old students) doesn't exactly represent the Mercedes-AMG target demographic.\\\\n\\\\n**My Contribution:** UX research and conceptual design. Together with teammates from sound design and technical engineering. 60-page research documentation. Presented to AMG leadership.","tags":["UX Research","Multisensory Design","Haptics"],"meta":{"partner":"Mercedes-Benz AMG","context":"HdM Stuttgart"},"imageAlt":"Project B.E.A.S.T.","features":{"1":{"title":"Light Choreography","desc":"Visual charging progress synced with audio \u2014 an ambient light show."},"2":{"title":"Haptic Signature","desc":"Vibration patterns matching AMG's pulse, felt through the cable."},"3":{"title":"Signature Sound","desc":"Emotive audio landscapes unique to AMG \u2014 the heartbeat reborn."},"4":{"title":"Sensed Progress","desc":"Multisensory feedback transforms waiting into an immersive experience."}}},"emobility":{"category":"Bachelor Thesis with Mercedes-Benz","title":"Connected E-Mobility \u2014 One Ecosystem, One Interface","description":"What if your car, wallbox, solar panels, and home grid finally spoke the same language? My bachelor thesis (graded 1.0) developed a connected e-mobility interface giving Mercedes customers the unified control their ecosystem deserves.","longDescription":"**The Challenge**\\\\n\\\\nThe shift to electromobility presents new challenges to the power grid and requires efficient energy management. Yet existing digital interfaces mostly focus only on the vehicle itself \u2014 seamless integration with home infrastructure and accessories is missing. The result: fragmented control, lack of transparency, jumping between isolated apps.\\\\n\\\\nThe central question of my bachelor thesis: How should a user interface be structured to enable multifunctional use and networking of electric vehicles with other products, and motivate users to actively engage?\\\\n\\\\n**1. Goal**\\\\n\\\\nDevelopment of a user-centered UI concept as a prototype for mobile devices. The concept should visualize central management of vehicle and accessories in a digital ecosystem \u2014 comfortable, efficient, and sustainable.\\\\n\\\\nCooperation partner: Mercedes-Benz Customer Solutions GmbH.\\\\n\\\\n**2. Methodology: User-Centered Design**\\\\n\\\\nUCD served as the methodological foundation. The iterative process included:\\\\n\\\\n- **Market Analysis:** 12 competitors analyzed (Mercedes me, Tesla, MyBMW, Bosch Smart Home)\\\\n- **User Research:** 4 personas created (Eco-Liz, Inno-Alex), expert interviews conducted, Card Sorting for validating information architecture\\\\n- **Conception & Prototyping:** Modular widget structure in Figma\\\\n- **Evaluation:** Qualitative user studies and UEQ-S questionnaire\\\\n\\\\n**3. Analysis and Research Findings**\\\\n\\\\nMarket analysis defined fundamental structures: central dashboard, clear onboarding processes, specific product areas.\\\\n\\\\n**Personas** reflected user needs: sustainability, innovation, efficiency/cost savings, everyday convenience.\\\\n\\\\n**Expert interviews** confirmed: clear structure, short navigation paths, simple operation, individual customization \u2014 plus desire for responsive display on smartwatches.\\\\n\\\\n**Card Sorting** validated architecture: Live status and quick access into dashboard, specific functions (vehicle control, charging settings) into separate areas.\\\\n\\\\n**4. Solution and Key Features**\\\\n\\\\nThe UI concept was prototyped modularly for consistent UX across different devices:\\\\n\\\\n- **Dashboard as Ecosystem Hub:** Live visualization of energy flow (generation, storage, consumption) from vehicle, charging infrastructure, and smart home. Current electricity price and weather support informed decisions.\\\\n- **Dynamic Island Integration:** Live charging status visible without opening the app\\\\n- **Charging Programs:** Predefined ('Smart', 'Eco') and individual settings (departure times, charging price) for optimization\\\\n- **Vehicle-to-Load (V2L):** Control of the vehicle as a mobile power source, including energy reservation and operating time visualization\\\\n- **Gamification:** Eco-score and progress indicators for sustainable behavior\\\\n\\\\n**5. Results and Validation**\\\\n\\\\n**UEQ-S Results:**\\\\n\\\\n- **Pragmatic Quality:** Processes (onboarding, navigation) rated as clear, understandable, and useful\\\\n- **Hedonic Quality:** Innovative features like V2L with 2.2/3 points \u2014 high interest and unique selling point potential\\\\n- **Ecosystem Networking:** Main reason for use among study participants\\\\n\\\\nEvery design decision grounded in research.\\\\n\\\\n**My Contribution:** Complete UI concept from information architecture to high-fidelity mockups. Graded 1.0.","tags":["UI Concept","IoT Ecosystem","Interaction Design"],"meta":{"partner":"Mercedes-Benz CS GmbH","keywords":"Efficiency \xB7 Responsive"},"imageAlt":"E-Mobility App Screen 1","imageAlt2":"E-Mobility App Screen 2","gallery":{"1":"Home screen \u2014 vehicle status, charge level, and energy overview at a glance","2":"Dynamic Island integration \u2014 live charging state visible without opening the app","3":"Energy dashboard \u2014 home, wallbox, and grid connected in one unified view","4":"Smart charging \u2014 departure-time planning optimises cost and green energy usage","5":"Modular menu \u2014 each function is its own widget, scaling from glance to full control"},"features":{"1":{"title":"Unified Control","desc":"One interface for all AMG EQ products \u2014 seamless switching, zero confusion."},"2":{"title":"Energy Intelligence","desc":"Smart optimization across devices, from vehicle to wallbox to grid."},"3":{"title":"Modular Scales","desc":"From compact widgets to full dashboards \u2014 information density adapts to context."},"4":{"title":"Future-Ready","desc":"Foundation architecture for next-generation connected mobility experiences."}}}}`);
